<TITLE> Lugovoy case is criminal, not intelligence matter: UK </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, May 31 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Britain's demand that Russian suspect Andrei Lugovoy stand trial for the murder of ex-spy Alexander Litvinenko is a criminal matter and not to do with intelligence issues, the government said on Thursday. "A request for the extradition of Mr Lugovoy to face trial in a UK court has been handed over. We await the formal Russian response," a Foreign Office spokesman said. "This is a criminal matter and is not an issue about intelligence. A British citizen was killed in London and UK citizens and visitors were put at risk.
